%N A099219 Decimal expansion of Li_5(1/2).
%D A099219 Alexander Apelblat, Tables of Integrals and Series, Harri Deutsch (1996), Section 1.3.2.
%H A099219 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-02462-8">(Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer International Publishing, 2019, section 4.49, pp. 306-307, section 5.49, p. 326, section 6.49, pp. 490-495.
%F A099219 Equals Sum_{k>0} 1/(2^k*k^5).
%F A099219 From _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 25 2026: (Start)
%F A099219 Equals (1/48) * Intergral_{x>=0} x^4/(exp(x)-1/2) dx.
%F A099219 Equals (1/6) * Intergral_{x=0..1} log(x)^3*log(1-x/2)/x dx. (End)
%F A099219 Equals Sum_{k>=1} H(k,4)/(k*2^(k+1)) + Sum_{k>=1} (-1)^(k+1) * (H(k)^4/48 + H(k,4)/8 + H(k)^2*H(k,2)/8 + H(k,2)^2/16 + H(k)*H(k,3)/6)/(k*(k + 1)), where H(k) = A001008(k)/A002805(k) is the k-th harmonic number, and H(k,2) = A007406(k)/A007407(k), H(k,3) = A007408(k)/A007409(k), and H(k,4) = A007410(k)/A007480(k) are the k-th generalized harmonic numbers of orders 2, 3, and 4, respectively (Vălean, 2019). - _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 16 2026
